getAnswer(uint256).return: The converted answer for `_roundId` of the `from` aggregator with the amount of precision as defined by `decimals`

getTimestamp(uint256).return: The timestamp of the `from` aggregator for the specified `_roundId`

latestAnswer().return: The converted answer with amount of precision as defined by `decimals`

latestRound().return: The value of latestRound for the `from` aggregator

latestTimestamp().return: The value of latestTimestamp for the `from` aggregator

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

setAddresses(uint8,address,address).details: Only callable by the owner of the contract

params._decimals: The number of decimals that the result will be returned with (should be specified for the `_to` aggregator)
params._from: The address of the aggregator contract which needs to be converted
params._to: The address of the aggregator contract which stores the rate to convert to

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params._newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

getAnswer(uint256).notice: Converts the specified answer for `_roundId` of the `from` aggregator to the latestAnswer of the `to` aggregator

getTimestamp(uint256).notice: Calls the `getTimestamp(_roundId)` function of the `from` aggregator for the specified `_roundId`

latestAnswer().notice: Converts the latest answer of the `from` aggregator to the rate of the `to` aggregator

latestRound().notice: Calls the `latestRound()` function of the `from` aggregator

latestTimestamp().notice: Calls the `latestTimestamp()` function of the `from` aggregator

renounceOwnership().notice: Renouncing to ownership will leave the contract without an owner. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.
